  "texts": [
    "Users of the benchmark should be aware of these context details when interpreting results.",
    "Furthermore, we are committed to updating the benchmark with more diverse datasets over time, to improve fairness and representativeness across the financial NLP tasks.",
    "Transparency and Data Documentation: In line with principles of research transparency and reproducibility, we provide detailed documentation for every dataset in the benchmark.",
    "This includes a description of how the data was collected, what the data consists of (e.g., \"10,000 financial news articles from 2010-2020, annotated with sentiment labels by experts\"), and any preprocessing steps we performed (such as removing certain fields or normalizing text).",
    "We also clearly state the intended use of the dataset and any limitations."
